bib_record.title: Energy spectra of secondary neutrons from the U-238(n,2n) and (n,3n) reactions (from threshold up to 15 MeV).

free_txt: The evaluation was based on inelastic level excitation
and evaporation data for U-238, U-237 and U-236. The
U-238 and U-236 data were retrieved from ENDF/B-IV,
and U-237 data were evaluated at Soreq, See VIEN-V0005
Extension of the compound nucleus mechanism for single
inelastic neutron emission to multiple inelastic
emissions is a successive, uninterrupted chain of
compound nuclei disintegrations.
A consistent way of making distinctions among the
different secondary neutrons is to consider separately
the neutrons emitted from the first, second, third
compound nucleus.
Inelastic spectra represented by evaporation formula,
P(E0 to E) = C * E * exp(-E/T(E0))
was used. T is nuclear temperature.
Threshold energy of U-238(n,2n) and U-238(n,3n) are
6.07 and 11.51 MeV, respectively. (ENDF/B-IV).
No error given
Evaluation
Approved by M.Caner, 1977/03/08.
Evaluation of energy spectra is based on,
1) Nuclear temperature of U-238, which is taken from
ENDF/B-IV,U-238 file (MAT 1262), evaluated by
N.C.Paik(1973)
2) Nuclear temperature of U-237, which is assumed
linear in (E)**1/2 and fitted at 2 points,
T(8 MeV) = 0.6 MeV, and T(0.7 MeV) = 0.27 MeV
3) Level excitation cross-sections of U-237 were
evaluated by the authors (see Appendix of
Nucl.Sci.Eng.59(1976)395). The numerical values are
compiled in VIEN-V0005.
Numerical values from Caner on a tape (part 1),
Eq.(11) in Nucl.Sci.Eng.,59(1976)395.
